# An outer list whose first element is a multi-line list does not gain
# a spurious trailing comma. The outer list itself has no direct
# newline intent (its `]` is on the same line as the last element), so
# no trailing comma should appear before the outer `]`. The inner list,
# which the user wrote multi-line, keeps its own trailing comma.
-- in.cue --
x: [[
	"go",
], b]
-- out/relpos --
x: [[
	"go",
], b]
-- out/norelpos --
x: [["go"], b]
